K+S May Receive Final Offers for Compo Unit Today, FTD Reports

-- B y   R i c h a r d   W e i s s
-- 
2011-05-13T14:58:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-13/k-s-may-receive-final-offers-for-compo-unit-today-ftd-reports.html
K+S AG expects final offers for its
Compo retail fertilizer unit today after a half-dozen suitors
reviewed it in the past six weeks, Financial Times Deutschland
reported, without saying where it got the information.  Among the suitors for the asset, which may fetch in excess
of 200 million euros ($285 million), are  Israel Chemicals Ltd. (ICL) ,
as well as Triton and One Equity Partners LLC, the newspaper
said in an online article.  Michael Wudonig, a spokesman for Kassel, Germany-based K+S,
declined to comment on the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Richard Weiss in Frankfurt at 
 rweiss5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net  